We recommended that the:

Municipal Accountant review the aforementioned transactions and effect the necessary adjustments in the books;

Municipal Treasurer initiate the transfer of funds to various affected depository accounts to correct the said erroneous check issuances.  Henceforth, exercise care in preparing checks to ensure that these are drawn from the correct depository accounts;

Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer thoroughly review the disbursements prior to the issuance of checks to avoid similar instance of juggling of funds;

MDRRMO observe the monthly submission of Report on the Sources and Utilization of Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund for monitoring of utilization of the MDRRMF and the implementation of DRRM-related PPAs; and

Municipal Mayor ensure that the yearly transfer of the unexpended balance of the current year’s MDRRMF and other provisions of COA Circular No. 2012-002 are strictly complied with.
